bug.short_desc: Media Writer couldn't create Live USB
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1204546 screenshot with error message
Description of problem: Media Writer couldn't create Live USB
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.97.1-0.fc25
Steps to Reproduce: Under Linux Fedora 25: 1) Install Fedora Media Writer with command: # dnf --enablerepo=updates-testing --refresh --best install mediawriter 2) Launch Fedora Media Writer 3) insert USB flash stick 4) Press "Create Live USB" button
Actual results: Media Writer after some time show error message.
This is caused by the selinux policies of your system. Either wait for their update or just switch to permissive mode (setenforce 0).
Also trying with # setenforce 0 this is not help solve problem.

Did you restart mediawriter after setenforce 0? If yes, then you either have broken udisks (storaged) or even dbus. Please inspect your journal or post the log from 5 minutes before you try mediawriter (journalctl --since -5m).
